Well, my 2022 work is wrapping up and I can’t help but reflect on this roller coaster of a year. It was full of many professional triumphs alongside a fair amount of heartache behind the scenes. However, I’m confident I will look back at this time as one of growth, connection and lots and lots of joy. I’m grateful to do what I do and be able to share it with you.

Will be sharing some highlights in subsequent posts. 💛 Take good care of yourselves as we head into the holidays.

In 2022, I had the pleasure of guest starring on the @nickelodeon series Warped! as C.C. Jacobs, renowned director of the “Space Conflicts” saga. ⭐️ 🚀 

I loved being on set with this rockstar cast @antonstarkman @kategodfrey @arianamolkara @its_chrismartinez @milancarter @josh_server and director Leonard R. Garner Jr. 

Many thanks @house.of.doro @adultingaccurately for having me!

@a3artistsagency @novatalentgroup

2022 was also the year I officially joined the #StarTrek universe! I was the voice of Boxy on the Star Trek: Prodigy episode “Preludes.” What a joy to work with voice director @brookchalmers and play opposite JASON MANTZOUKAS (though we didn’t get to record together) who has brought our home hours of laughter on @hdtgm. 

@a3artistsagency @novatalentgroup

In 2022 I made my @geffenplayhouse debut in @schatzmatt’s beautiful musical A Wicked Soul in Cherry Hill, directed by the wonderfully supportive and insightful @mike.m.donahue. 

Practically a summer camp of ADVENTURE and music making with these gorgeous humans and fellow soldiers @dannyrothman @nmongiardo @jahbrilcook @jillsobule @rivkah.reyes @ohthatscottanthony @mister_8th_wonder @thejohnicles @nicole_marcus @thejimmykieffer @mrclarkmoore @oprahwinfreckle @iamfrandeleon @aescalante88 @yourstrulymissjulie @jillgsm and so many more friends for life. 

Thank you to all my family and friends who came out to see us!!

@a3artistsagency @novatalentgroup

A huge highlight of 2022, I joined the Marvel universe—as Xandarian Reporter Felician Erazal in the Guardians of the Galaxy: Cosmic Rewind attraction at @waltdisneyworld  Epcot!

I appeared as Felician on @goodmorningamerica to chat with host @ashan about the ride (in which I interview the Guardians themselves.) 

My favorite part of this experience (besides friends texting me when they are on the ride) was hanging with the brilliant @colorbyspiegel and learning about how his team develops Disney attractions behind-the-scenes. SO GRATEFUL to @waltdisneyimagineering for this once in a lifetime experience!

Merry Christmas and happy everything. Life is good. ❤️

Since my mother brought me here at age nine, I’ve been bewitched by the Tower of London and the stories of (horrific) history held within. 

As an American of Indian and Pakistani descent, my relationship with Britain is an oft complicated one (see last slide.) But it was nice to return here after so many years—a place that feels strangely like home, alive with history, reflections on our mortality and the complex and beautiful ways we are all remembered. 

Thank you @barryjneely for taking this photo of me between the site of Queen Anne Boleyn’s execution and her resting site in the Chapel of St Peter ad Vincula.

Ranis always rise. 

A photo series I am fondly calling “Birthright.” 👑 

Happy Independence Day to India and Pakistan.

My mother died suddenly when I was a teenager. It’s not something I talk about much, because to be quite frank, it was the worst time of my life. But today, 25 years later, I feel like I’m finally starting to believe I’m not cursed and defined solely by this tragedy. That life is full and rich and I can be violently, unabashedly, incandescently happy. This happy  life belongs to me, fully. And if you’re part of this very sucky club to have lost a parent at such a young age, I want to tell you that I see you and I love you and I get it. And I hope you will someday believe a happy life belongs to you, too. 💗

Thank you, mommy. You left quite a legacy. 💗
